Mexico peso speculation eases slightly mid - morning . Pressure on Mexican peso contracts had eased slightly by mid - morning on Thursday . Nonetheless , the peso was still toying with the eight - per - dollar mark as the market braced itself for the U . S . House of Representatives vote on decertifying Mexico as a drug war ally , traders said . " The peso opened under great pressure , then some stepped in to sell ( dollars ) , " a trader said . The benchmark 48 - hour peso and its 24 - hour counterpart stood 3 . 2 and 2 . 5 centavos weaker , respectively , at 7 . 9980 / 8 . 0020 and 7 . 9860 / 7 . 9910 per dollar . 
